
* An environment variable ECHO_LOCATION is looked for when Echo tries
  to find the location of your predfined agents, sites and worlds. The
  directory that it gives should contain 3 directories, "agents",
  "sites" and "worlds".

* Optional are variables ECHO_WORLD, ECHO_SITE and ECHO_AGENT which can
  be used to specify a woirld, site and agent that will appear in the
  three editor windows when the program comes up.
